OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782125278
OL,3,CPeston: Does Labour need a leadership
OL,4,Ccontest if Burnham is expected to win
OL,5,Cit?
OL,7,FPeter Kyle was explicit that he does
OL,8,Fnot want a coronation of Andy Burnham,
OL,9,Fthat a leadership contest that debates
OL,10,Fhow Labour can best hold Reform at bay
OL,11,Fwould be preferable, but that the
OL,12,Ftransition from Keir Starmer to a new
OL,13,Fprime minister must be "functional"
OL,14,Fand orderly.
OL,16,FThe implication of this - and of
OL,17,Fconversations I have had with other
OL,18,Fministers - is that Starmer will
OL,19,Fannounce a date for his departure
OL,20,Ftomorrow.
OL,26,@uD@XOUuD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
